"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_zjlab_fe_data_hub_ui=self.webpackChunk_zjlab_fe_data_hub_ui||[]).push([[930],{27930:(n,t,e)=>{e.d(t,{default:()=>r});const r='# TipTap Editor Component\r\n\r\nA powerful, feature-rich rich text editor component built on top of [TipTap](https://tiptap.dev/) and React. This component provides both an editable editor and a read-only reader for displaying rich text content.\r\n\r\n## Features\r\n\r\n### âœ¨ Rich Text Editing\r\n- **Text Formatting**: Bold, italic, underline, strikethrough\r\n- **Headings**: H1, H2, H3, H4 support\r\n- **Lists**: Bullet lists and numbered lists\r\n- **Text Alignment**: Left, center, right alignment\r\n- **Colors**: Text color and highlight/background color\r\n- **Links**: Insert and edit hyperlinks\r\n- **Code**: Inline code and code blocks with syntax highlighting\r\n- **Blockquotes**: Quote blocks for citations\r\n- **Horizontal Rules**: Divider lines\r\n\r\n### ðŸ“ Content Elements\r\n- **Images**: Upload and insert images (base64 support)\r\n- **Tables**: Insert and edit resizable tables with headers\r\n- **Markdown**: Full Markdown support with auto-detection on paste\r\n\r\n### ðŸŽ¨ User Interface\r\n- **Toolbar**: Comprehensive top toolbar with all formatting options\r\n- **Bubble Menu**: Context menu that appears when text is selected\r\n- **Floating Menu**: Quick insert menu that appears on empty lines\r\n- **Responsive**: Works seamlessly across different screen sizes\r\n\r\n### ðŸ”§ Developer Experience\r\n- **Ref API**: Imperative handle for programmatic control\r\n- **Change Callbacks**: `onChange` prop for content updates\r\n- **Multiple Formats**: Get content as HTML, JSON, or Markdown\r\n- **Editable/Read-only Modes**: Switch between editing and viewing modes\r\n\r\n## Installation\r\n\r\nThis component requires the following dependencies:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  "@tiptap/react": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/starter-kit": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-text-align": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-highlight": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-color": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-text-style": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-image": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-table": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-table-row": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-table-cell": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-table-header": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-code-block-lowlight": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/extension-placeholder": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "@tiptap/markdown": "^2.x.x",\r\n  "lowlight": "^3.x.x"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Components\r\n\r\n### TipTapEditor\r\n\r\nThe main editable editor component.\r\n\r\n#### Props\r\n\r\n| Prop | Type | Default | Description |\r\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\r\n| `content` | `string` | `\'\'` | Initial HTML content |\r\n| `placeholder` | `string` | `\'å¼€å§‹è¾“å…¥å†…å®¹...\'` | Placeholder text when editor is empty |\r\n| `editable` | `boolean` | `true` | Whether the editor is editable |\r\n| `autofocus` | `boolean` | `false` | Auto-focus the editor on mount |\r\n| `className` | `string` | `\'\'` | Additional CSS class for the editor container |\r\n| `toolbarClassName` | `string` | `\'\'` | Additional CSS class for the toolbar |\r\n| `onChange` | `(html: string) => void` | `undefined` | Callback fired when content changes |\r\n\r\n#### Ref Methods\r\n\r\nThe component exposes an imperative handle via `ref` with the following methods:\r\n\r\n```typescript\r\ninterface TipTapEditorHandle {\r\n  getContent: () => string;        // Get HTML content\r\n  getJSON: () => Record<string, unknown>;  // Get JSON representation\r\n  getMarkdown: () => string;       // Get Markdown content\r\n  setContent: (content: string) => void;  // Set HTML content\r\n  setMarkdown: (markdown: string) => void; // Set Markdown content\r\n  focus: () => void;               // Focus the editor\r\n  isEmpty: () => boolean;          // Check if editor is empty\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Example Usage\r\n\r\n```tsx\r\nimport { useRef } from \'react\';\r\nimport TipTapEditor, { type TipTapEditorHandle } from \'@/components/tip-tap\';\r\n\r\nfunction MyComponent() {\r\n  const editorRef = useRef<TipTapEditorHandle>(null);\r\n\r\n  const handleSave = () => {\r\n    const content = editorRef.current?.getContent();\r\n    console.log(\'Saved content:\', content);\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  const handleLoad = () => {\r\n    editorRef.current?.setContent(\'<p>Hello World</p>\');\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  return (\r\n    <div>\r\n      <TipTapEditor\r\n        ref={editorRef}\r\n        content="<p>Initial content</p>"\r\n        placeholder="Start typing..."\r\n        onChange={(html) => {\r\n          console.log(\'Content changed:\', html);\r\n        }}\r\n      />\r\n      <button onClick={handleSave}>Save</button>\r\n      <button onClick={handleLoad}>Load</button>\r\n    </div>\r\n  );\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### TipTapReader\r\n\r\nA read-only component for displaying rich text content.\r\n\r\n#### Props\r\n\r\n| Prop | Type | Default | Description |\r\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\r\n| `content` | `string` | **required** | HTML content to display |\r\n| `className` | `string` | `\'\'` | Additional CSS class |\r\n\r\n#### Example Usage\r\n\r\n```tsx\r\nimport { TipTapReader } from \'@/components/tip-tap\';\r\n\r\nfunction MyComponent() {\r\n  const content = \'<h1>Title</h1><p>Some content</p>\';\r\n\r\n  return (\r\n    <TipTapReader content={content} />\r\n  );\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Features Breakdown\r\n\r\n### Toolbar\r\n\r\nThe toolbar provides quick access to all formatting options:\r\n\r\n- **History**: Undo/Redo\r\n- **Text Formatting**: Bold, Italic, Underline, Strikethrough\r\n- **Headings**: Dropdown for H1-H4\r\n- **Colors**: Text color and highlight color pickers\r\n- **Alignment**: Left, Center, Right\r\n- **Lists**: Bullet and numbered lists\r\n- **Block Elements**: Blockquote, Code block, Horizontal rule\r\n- **Media**: Link, Image, Table insertion\r\n\r\n### Bubble Menu\r\n\r\nAppears when text is selected, providing quick formatting options:\r\n- Bold, Italic, Underline, Strikethrough\r\n- Highlight\r\n- Link insertion/editing\r\n\r\n### Floating Menu\r\n\r\nAppears on empty lines, allowing quick insertion of:\r\n- Headings (H1, H2, H3)\r\n- Lists (Bullet, Numbered)\r\n- Blockquote\r\n- Code block\r\n- Horizontal rule\r\n- Image\r\n- Table\r\n\r\n## File Structure\r\n\r\n```\r\ntip-tap/\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ index.tsx                 # Main exports\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ editor.tsx                # TipTapEditor component\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ reader.tsx                # TipTapReader component\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ bubble-menu.tsx           # Bubble menu component\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ floating-menu.tsx         # Floating menu component\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ toolbar/\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ index.tsx            # Main toolbar component\r\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ components/          # Toolbar sub-components\r\nâ”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ color-picker.tsx\r\nâ”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ heading-dropdown.tsx\r\nâ”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ image-button.tsx\r\nâ”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ link-button.tsx\r\nâ”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ table-button.tsx\r\nâ”‚       â””â”€â”€ toolbar-button.tsx\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ extensions/\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ index.ts             # Extension configurations\r\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ markdown-paste.ts    # Markdown paste handler\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ icons/\r\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ index.tsx            # Icon components\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ styles/\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ editor.css           # Editor styles\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ content.css          # Content styles\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ toolbar.css          # Toolbar styles\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ menus.css            # Menu styles\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ animations.css       # Animation styles\r\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ variables.css        # CSS variables\r\nâ””â”€â”€ demo/\r\n    â””â”€â”€ index.tsx            # Demo/example usage\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Styling\r\n\r\nThe component includes comprehensive CSS styles. You can customize the appearance by:\r\n\r\n1. **CSS Variables**: Modify variables in `styles/variables.css`\r\n2. **Custom Classes**: Use `className` and `toolbarClassName` props\r\n3. **Override Styles**: Target the component\'s CSS classes in your own stylesheets\r\n\r\nKey CSS classes:\r\n- `.tip-tap-editor` - Main editor container\r\n- `.tip-tap-editor__content` - Editor content area\r\n- `.tip-tap-reader` - Reader container\r\n- `.tip-tap-toolbar` - Toolbar container\r\n- `.tip-tap-bubble-menu` - Bubble menu\r\n- `.tip-tap-floating-menu` - Floating menu\r\n\r\n## Advanced Usage\r\n\r\n### Programmatic Content Manipulation\r\n\r\n```tsx\r\nconst editorRef = useRef<TipTapEditorHandle>(null);\r\n\r\n// Get content in different formats\r\nconst html = editorRef.current?.getContent();\r\nconst json = editorRef.current?.getJSON();\r\nconst markdown = editorRef.current?.getMarkdown();\r\n\r\n// Set content\r\neditorRef.current?.setContent(\'<p>New content</p>\');\r\neditorRef.current?.setMarkdown(\'# Title\\n\\nContent\');\r\n\r\n// Check if empty\r\nconst isEmpty = editorRef.current?.isEmpty();\r\n\r\n// Focus editor\r\neditorRef.current?.focus();\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Switching Between Edit and Read Modes\r\n\r\n```tsx\r\nconst [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(true);\r\nconst [content, setContent] = useState(\'\');\r\n\r\nreturn (\r\n  <>\r\n    {isEditing ? (\r\n      <TipTapEditor\r\n        content={content}\r\n        onChange={setContent}\r\n      />\r\n    ) : (\r\n      <TipTapReader content={content} />\r\n    )}\r\n    <button onClick={() => setIsEditing(!isEditing)}>\r\n      {isEditing ? \'View\' : \'Edit\'}\r\n    </button>\r\n  </>\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Read-only Editor\r\n\r\n```tsx\r\n<TipTapEditor\r\n  content={content}\r\n  editable={false}\r\n/>\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Extensions\r\n\r\nThe component uses the following TipTap extensions:\r\n\r\n- **StarterKit**: Core editing functionality\r\n- **TextAlign**: Text alignment\r\n- **Highlight**: Text highlighting\r\n- **Color**: Text color\r\n- **TextStyle**: Text styling support\r\n- **Image**: Image insertion\r\n- **Table**: Table support (with row, cell, header)\r\n- **CodeBlockLowlight**: Syntax-highlighted code blocks\r\n- **Placeholder**: Placeholder text\r\n- **Markdown**: Markdown parsing and serialization\r\n- **MarkdownPaste**: Auto-detect and parse pasted Markdown\r\n\r\n## Browser Support\r\n\r\nThe component supports all modern browsers that support:\r\n- ES6+\r\n- CSS Grid/Flexbox\r\n- FileReader API (for image uploads)\r\n\r\n## License\r\n\r\nThis component is part of the data-hub-ui project.\r\n\r\n'}}]);